{
  "title":"The Age of Reason",
  "date":"2010-05-01 CST",
  "origin":"Funny Logic",
  "url":"text-the-age-of-reason",
  "author":"Ryan X. Charles"
}




<p>&#8220;I inferred there was a 99% probability, so I went ahead and bumped it up to 100%,&#8221; she said.</p>

<p>&#8220;What?&#8221; he said. &#8220;There is no rational basis for bumping probabilities like that. You&#8217;re just being lazy.&#8221;</p>

<p>&#8220;You&#8217;re right,&#8221; she said, stopping to think for a minute. &#8220;I don&#8217;t know what I was thinking.&#8221;</p>

<p>Kids in the future are so rational.</p>

